butter box tree
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:the white pine or kahikatea, considered free of tainting of taste and odour,  used for making boxes for transporting butter to Britain.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: also butterbox, butter box timber, butterbox timber, butter box wood, butterbox wood
